[{"id":"VR792800","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<div><div class=\"stimulus_reference\"><div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows a diagram of a horizontal slab and a horizontal sheet in parallel. The slab is above the sheet, and is labeled “Conducting Slab, Zero net charge,” and the sheet is labeled “Insulating Sheet, Uniformly Charged.” Point X is located one centimeter above the top surface of the slab, and Point Y is located 1 centimeter below the sheet. Points X and Y have the same horizontal position. The slab has thickness 1 centimeter, and the separation between the slab and the sheet is 2 centimeters.\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/578/VR792800.g01.svg\"/></div></div></div><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">A thin, insulating sheet with a positive uniform charge density is near a thick, conducting slab that has zero net charge, as shown in the figure. Both the thin sheet and the thick slab are very large. The insulting sheet is <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2 centimeters\"><math alttext=\"2 centimeters\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn><mspace width=\"0.2em\"></mspace><mi>cm</mi></math></span></span> from the conducting slab, and the slab is <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1 centimeter\"><math alttext=\"1 centimeter\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>1</mn><mspace width=\"0.2em\"></mspace><mi>cm</mi></math></span></span> thick. Also shown are two labeled points: Point <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"X\"><math alttext=\"X\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">X</mi></math></span></span>, which is <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1 centimeter\"><math alttext=\"1 centimeter\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>1</mn><mspace width=\"0.2em\"></mspace><mi>cm</mi></math></span></span> above the slab, and Point <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"Y\"><math alttext=\"Y\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Y</mi></math></span></span>, which is <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1 centimeter\"><math alttext=\"1 centimeter\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>1</mn><mspace width=\"0.2em\"></mspace><mi>cm</mi></math></span></span> below the sheet. If the electric field at the surface of the thin sheet has a magnitude of <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"100 newtons per coulomb\"><math alttext=\"100 newtons per coulomb\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>100</mn><mspace width=\"0.25em\"></mspace><mtext>N</mtext><mo>/</mo><mtext>C</mtext></math></span></span>, what is the magnitude of the electric potential difference between points <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"X\"><math alttext=\"X\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">X</mi></math></span></span> and <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"Y\"><math alttext=\"Y\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Y</mi></math></span></span>?</p>\n","rubricRef":"VR792800_rubric","choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2 volts\"><math alttext=\"2 volts\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn><mspace width=\"0.2em\"></mspace><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">V</mi></math></span></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"3 volts\"><math alttext=\"3 volts\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>3</mn><mspace width=\"0.2em\"></mspace><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">V</mi></math></span></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"4 volts\"><math alttext=\"4 volts\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>4</mn><mspace width=\"0.2em\"></mspace><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">V</mi></math></span></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"5 volts\"><math alttext=\"5 volts\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>5</mn><mspace width=\"0.2em\"></mspace><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">V</mi></math></span></span></p>"],"answer":0}]